            ("Isn't O-negative the universal donor?", "O-negative is the universal donor for red blood cells, not plasma. Plasma is the opposite: AB is universal for plasma because it lacks anti-A and anti-B antibodies. The rule flips because red-cell compatibility depends on antigens while plasma compatibility depends on antibodies."),
            ("Does my blood type affect how much I get paid for plasma?", "No. Standard plasma compensation is based on your donation visit, current bonuses, and often your body weight &mdash; not your blood type. Two donors of the same weight at the same center earn the same regardless of ABO or Rh type."),
